text:
It was empty of customers Saturday lunch time, so service was nice and fast.
The size of 6 pieces was quite impressive and a good amount of kinako powder given. The texture was slightly softer than I prefer, but  overall enjoyable.

Located in the basement just outside NTUC Finest. Quite a nice place to sit at for a dessert after a meal. The warabi-mochi while quite decent, still canâ€™t beat the one in the next building. Not as fragrant and the texture isnâ€™t as nice also. The seating area is nicer here though.

Went early on a weekend, the ambience was nice and peaceful and the cashier was friendly. I ordered the original warabi set. I like the texture. It was soft but still abit chewable and the kinako powder was generous. It's a good hideout at town area to relax from all the mad shopping.
